===Pronunciation===
*līt, /laɪt/, /<tt>laIt</tt>/
*:'''Homophones''': [[lite]]
*:[[Rhymes:English:-aɪt|Rhymes: -aɪt]]

===Etymology 1===
==== Verb ====
'''to light''' ('''lights''', '''lit''' ''or'' '''lighted''', '''lit''' ''or'' '''lighted''', '''lighting''')

# to [[start]] a [[fire]]
# to [[illuminate]]

=====Usage note=====
As a predicative adjective, ''lighted'' is more usual than ''lit''. So, for example, "a lighted candle" is more usual than "a lit candle".

===== Synonyms =====
